HEADWORD: Chanticleer
<hw>Chan"ti*cleer</hw> <pr>(ch⟦acr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧*kl⟦emac⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <etsep>Chanteclair</etsep>, name of the cock in
the <ets>Roman du Renart</ets> (<ets>Reynard the Fox</ets>);
<ets>chanter</ets> to chant + <ets>clair</ets> clear. See
<er>Chant</er>, and <er>Clear</er>.]</ety> <def>A cock, so called from
the clearness or loudness of his voice in crowing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chanting</ent>⟦br⟧
